Corona in the states of America and in the provinces in The Netherlands

Pieter Hobbelen

20-6-2020

Below we see a figure about the amount of Corona patients in each state, Washington DC and the American territories*. The X-axis represents the population in millions of the state, and the Y-axis represents the amount of Corona patients in the states and the territories. We see also 10 regions, 7 of them are ‘normal’ regions based on the North, East, South and West. The other three are the regions ‘Alaska’, the ‘Pacific Islands’ and the ‘Atlantic Islands’. To see in which region a state or a territory is located you can scroll in the table below, you can also see the official abbreviation, you will need these to read the figure below.

  • The American territories are Puerto Rico and the American Virgin Islands in the Caribbean, Guam, the Northern Mariana Islands and American Samoa.

When we look at the picture we see all the 56 states or territories and the black line indicates the average of the United States. When a state is above the line, that state has a relative high confirmed cases rate, and when a state is located under the line that state has a relatively low confirmed rate. We see that New York (NY) and New Jersey (NJ) are outliers, they have a very high confirmed cases rate. Florida (FL), Texas (TX) and California (CA) are the opposite, their Corona patient density is very low. Some labels off states are overlapping eachother, the smaller states. In the next figure I’m gonna solve that the labels off the smaller states are overlapping eachother by choosing another scale on the X-axis. The problem is that there are only 4 states with a population bigger or equal to 20 million people. So the right side of the figure has 4 labels and the left side the other 52 labels. The solution is to choose a X-scale that is in a logarithmic scale, a scale where 0 to 1 is the same size as 1 to 10 and 10 to 100. So we make the X-scale logarithmic with base 10 (log10). Instead of an average USA line we use another method to determine the normal states. I the second figure we see a blue line and a grey area around that line, that area indicates the area where a ‘normal’ USA state is located. We see that the outliers are New York (NY), New Jersey (NJ), Illinois (IL), Massachusetts (MA), Connecticut (CT), Louisiana (LA) and Maryland (MD) with a higher confirmed rate than usual. The ouliers when it comes to a lower confirmed rate than usual are Ohio (OH), Montana (MO), the state Washington (WA), North Carolina (NC), Georgia (GA), Florida (FL) and Texas (TX). We see that California is no outlier now, probably because there is no state to compare the population with. When there is no stata to compare the values of California with, the line and area that indicates the normal value is going to California values.

Now we are going to make the same two plots, so one plot in a normal continious X-scale and another one in a logaratmic X-scale with base 10 (log 10). We are going to plot data for each state, but this time we want to see in stead of the confirmed cases the amount of deaths due to Corona. Note that it is impossible to know for sure that the deathcase is actually Corona but we use the data that is probably the amount of deaths due to Corona. When we plot the figure we see again that New York has an extreme high rate, whether it is about confirmed cases or death cases. When we are going to look at outliers the outliers are almost the same states. The outliers with a higher death rate are Connecticut (CT), Louisiana (LA), Massachusetts (MA), New Jersey (NJ) and New York (NY), so Illinois (IL) and Maryland (MD) are now located in the ‘normal’ area. The outliers with a lower death rate than normal are Tennessee (TN), Virginia (VA), Georgia (GA) Ohio (OH), North Carolina (NC), Florida (FL) and Texas (TX). We did not see some big change somewhere, like that the location of the states is very much changed. The place has remained about the same compared to the other states.

When we look at the first figure and the ouliers with an higher confirmed rate than usual, it looks like that the majority of the outliers are located in the North East region. When we look at the second figure see the actual outliers, there are 7 outliers with a higher rate. Connecticut, Massachusetts, New Jersey, New York, Maryland are outliers in the region North East and the other two are Louisiana in the South Mid region and Illinois in the Mid region.

In the next 6 figures we do the same thing, but instead of the data for the United States and the American Territories, we use the data for The Netherlands. The RIVM, the official publisher for the Corona data for The Netherlands, provides also the data about the confirmed cases and the death cases, but they provide also data about the hospital cases (the Intensive Care patients). In The Netherlands there are instead of 50 states 12 provinces. We see again in the first figure 12 points represinting the provinces and a black line representing the average for The Netherlands. We that there are almost no outliers, maybe Noord-Brabant and Limburg. When we look at the next figure, we see again a line, but this time also an area that indicates the area where a ‘normal’ province is located. We see that Noord- Brabant is located on the border and has a slightly higher confirmed rate, and Noord-Holland is also located on the border and has a small slightly lower confirmed rate.

We see again the same figures, the amount of deaths per state in a continious X-scale and in a logarithmic X-scale. When we compare the locations of the provinces in the figure with the locations of the provinces in the figures with the confirmed cases (figures e and f) we see that Noord-Brabant further away from the avarage line, compared to the changes of the other provinces. So, the ratio that indicates the probability of how many patients died due to Corona, given that the patient has Corona, is high in Noord-Brabant compared to the other provinces. Another thing that we see is that Gelderland is below the average line in the death cases figure, and located on the line in the confirmed cases figure. So the probability that a patient died due to Corona, given that the patient has Corona, is low in Gelderland.
